The President of Pentecostal Ministers Forum of Nigeria, bishop Chidi Anthony recently celebrated his birthday with friends, families and well-Wishers. It was indeed an opportunity for many to felicitate with the man who has made an indelible mark in the body of Christ. Speaking at the event, Mr. Greg Omelu, a friend, described the bishop as a vessel that God is using to the benefit of mankind;Apostle N. C Michael who happens to be the vice president of PMF described the bishop as a man of honour, he recalled that he actually dedicated the first child of the Bishop. Apostle Alex Ogonnaya described him as someone who is always available during difficult and precarious situations. Speaking during the celebration which was held at his residence, Isheri Oshun, the cleric implored the government to provide employment opportunities for the youths in order to help ameliorate the tense condition in the country, he said: “any nation that has a massive number of unemployed youths is trouble, we are actually breeding monsters these days; crime and other vices that we are experiencing these days is because of this, if we engage our youths and they have a meaningful source of income, insecurity and other vices will reduce drastically”. The Abia state coordinator of PMF, Rev. Ben Nkwocha who was also present at the event described Bishop Anthony as a great friend and brother; other clerics that were present at the event, Apostle Azubuike John Chinemere, Major, prophet Chika and others. In his closing remarks, the Bishop was full of gratitude to the Almighty God for preserving him and making his celebration a reality, he said: “I want to thank God for his mercies and love, I also want to thank everyone that honoured this event, I pray that God Almighty will honour you all”.